<figureCitation id="F0E9C08DFFC72B61DD6DFD80FF27FD00" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="33.[189,232,1845,1871]" captionTargetBox="[209,1349,1193,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-18@33.[189,1398,1169,1808]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Fig. 22. Apical part of male metafemur, lateral view. A–C. Merodon lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. Paratypes. A. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_052). B. Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_060). Specimen FSUNS (FSUNS ID ZA6_066). D–F. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. D. Holotype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25089). E. Paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). F. Paratype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25090). Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013054/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">Fig. 22D– F</figureCitation>
). The triangular lamina is more or less dentate, and the apical dens is distinct (
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DCC2FD6CFA99FD07" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" box="[1199,1391,665,691]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DCC2FD6CFA99FD07" box="[1199,1391,665,691]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61D8D0FD4BFE7FFD63" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[189,393,701,727]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61D8D0FD4BFE7FFD63" box="[189,393,701,727]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61D9FAFD4BFDE3FD62" authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[407,533,701,726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61D9FAFD4BFDE3FD62" box="[407,533,701,726]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4195BD61FFC72B61DA71FD4BFD8EFD62" box="[540,632,701,727]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) or less distinct, as in 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DBEDFD4BFC16FD63" authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[896,992,701,727]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DBEDFD4BFC16FD63" box="[896,992,701,727]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. lotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4195BD61FFC72B61DB8AFD4BFBB4FD63" box="[999,1090,701,727]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DC16FD4BFB0CFD62" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1915" box="[1147,1274,701,726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasicus">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DC16FD4BFB0CFD62" box="[1147,1274,701,726]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. nasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A scutum with conspicuous pollinose vittae, and terga with pollinose posterior margin and medial fasciae, are characters present in most species, except 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DAC2FCF2FCF9FCA9" authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[687,783,771,797]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DAC2FCF2FCF9FCA9" box="[687,783,771,797]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. lotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4195BD61FFC72B61DB7AFCF2FC82FCAA" box="[791,884,772,798]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, characterized by the absence of pollinosity on thorax and abdomen (in females a pair of indistinct pollinose fasciae on tergum 4). Width and shape of vittae and fasciae on scutum and terga vary, especially in 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DB10FCBCFBBFFCD7" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[893,1097,841,867]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DB10FCBCFBBFFCD7" box="[893,1097,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DC3AFCBCFB20FCD7" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1915" box="[1111,1238,842,867]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasicus">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DC3AFCBCFB20FCD7" box="[1111,1238,842,867]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. nasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DD63FCBCFA80FCD7" authority="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan, 2021" authorityName="Vujić &amp; Radenković &amp; Zorić &amp; Likov &amp; Tot &amp; Veselić &amp; Djan" authorityYear="2021" box="[1294,1398,841,867]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zebra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DD63FCBCFA80FCD7" box="[1294,1398,841,867]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. zebra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4195BD61FFC72B61D8D0FC9BFEE0FC33" box="[189,278,877,903]" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The colour of the postpronotum, lateral sides of scutum, frons and face in 
<taxonomicName id="AFD2A78BFFC72B61DC1DFC9BFACDFC33" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1939" box="[1136,1339,877,903]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="122" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multifasciatus">
<emphasis id="5AA6001AFFC72B61DC1DFC9BFACDFC33" box="[1136,1339,877,903]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">M. multifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vary from reddish-brown to black. Specimens from the south of the range (
<collectingCountry id="10C59C98FFC72B61DB9DFC66FBDAFC1E" box="[1008,1068,912,938]" name="South Africa" pageId="34" pageNumber="122">RSA</collectingCountry>
) are darker than individuals from northern parts (Central Africa).
